# Walkthrough: Documentation Audit & GitHub Update (v0.4.0)

I have completed a comprehensive audit of all project documentation to reflect the recent **Native Web Component** refactor and the new **Smart Regions & Popularity** features.

## Key Changes

### 1. Version Bump & Standardization

- Bumped project version to **v0.4.0** across:
  - [pyproject.toml](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/pyproject.toml)
  - [src/zget/cli.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/cli.py)
  - `src/get/mcp/server.py`
- Updated copyright year to **2026** in [LICENSE](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/LICENSE).
- Standardized terminology: **"Webport"** has been replaced with **"The Portal"** consistently across the codebase and documentation.

### 2. Terminology Sanitization

- Removed references to **"Digital Intelligence Ecosystem"** as per user preference.
- Focused branding on the core triad: **The Archivist**, **The Vault**, and **The Portal**.

### 3. Documentation Updates

- [README.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/README.md): Completely modernized to highlight the "Zero-Build" native component architecture and intelligence features.
- [AGENTS.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/AGENTS.md): Updated to reflect the modular component structure for better AI assistant engagement.
- [openspec/project.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/openspec/project.md): Updated tech stack and design principles to include Native Web Components.

### 4. Recognition

- Added natural acknowledgments for the **yt-dlp** community and the **Gemini** and **Antigravity** teams at Google DeepMind.

### 5. Repository Cleanup

- Removed redundant files: `sw.js`, `openspec/AGENTS.md`, and [src/zget/server/portal/README.md](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/portal/README.md).
- Cleaned up development artifacts: `server.log` and `data/failed_sites.txt`.
- Hardened [.gitignore](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/.gitignore) to prevent leakage of runtime data (`health_log.json`, `Downloads/`) and AI infrastructure files (`.gemini/`, `.agent/`).

### 6. Portal Pivot: Command Center & Registry

- **Unified Ingest**: Moved the URL archive bar into the global header. It's now persistent and easily accessible.
- **Intelligence Registry**: Pivoted the 'Regions' view into a **Site Intelligence Registry**. It displays platform health, global prominence, and discovery categories in a more compact, useful layout.
- **Event-Driven Refresh**: Archiving a new URL now automatically refreshes the Vault view once the download is queued.

![New Portal Command Center](/Users/base/.gemini/antigravity/brain/96534431-eec5-45ce-b60c-0118b51f4eb0/header_and_registry_view_1767511876205.png)

